Basically I just got sick of accidentally opening the legacy tray,
but I still wanted it there. So I just cranked up the threshold a bit.

The extension is licensed under LGPL 2.1 or later.

Hide Legacy Tray
================
I essentially copied this from Jonny Lamb's extension Hide Legacy Tray
extension.

You can install it here: http://extensions.gnome.org/extension/967

Source: http://github.com/jonnylamb/shell-hide-legacy-tray/
